TEHRAN, Islamic Republic of Iran, April 19, 2022/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            Iranian Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian has sent a message to South Africa’s Minister of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation Ms. Naledi Pandor, expressing sympathy on the floods in the country that left hundreds of people in different areas of South Africa dead or displaced.



Iranian Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian has sent a message to South Africa’s Minister of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation Ms. Naledi Pandor, expressing sympathy on the floods in the country that left hundreds of people in different areas of South Africa dead or displaced.

Amir Abdollahian offered his condolences to the bereaved families, the government of South Africa as well as his counterpart and prayed that patience be bestowed upon the victims’ families and those hurt in the incident.